text: Nina Davis (born December 7, 1994) is an American women's basketball player. Davis represented the United States at the 2015 Summer Universiade. Davis was awarded the Big 12 Conference Women's Basketball Player of the Year as a sophomore at Baylor. Despite scoring over 2,000 points and grabbing over 1,000 rebounds during her career, Davis went undrafted in the 2017 WNBA Draft.
